<task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.2" id="uploading-modules"><title>Upload modules</title><shortdesc>To help fix vulnerabilities on nodes, upload modules published on the&#160;<ph conkeyref="ProductNames/puppet"/> <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/forge"/>. The module must contain a task.</shortdesc><prolog><author translate="no" type="creator">Eamonn Smith &lt;eamonn.smith@puppet.com&gt;</author></prolog><taskbody><context>Modules are self-contained bundles of code and data. Each module manages a specific task in your infrastructure, such as installing and configuring a piece of software. For more information, see <xref href="https://puppet.com/docs/puppet/latest/modules_fundamentals.html" scope="external">Module fundamentals</xref>. </context><steps><step><cmd>Download a module from the <xref href="https://forge.puppet.com/" scope="external"><ph conkeyref="ProductNames/forge"/></xref>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>On the sidebar, click <uicontrol>Manage tasks</uicontrol>, and then click <uicontrol>Add tasks</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Click <uicontrol>Upload a module</uicontrol>, choose the module you just downloaded from the <ph conkeyref="ProductNames/forge"/>.</cmd><info><p><note type="important">The name of your module needs to follow the default download format.</note></p></info></step><step><cmd>Click <uicontrol>Add details</uicontrol>.</cmd></step><step><cmd>Click <uicontrol>Save task</uicontrol>.</cmd><info><p>The <uicontrol>Settings</uicontrol> page appears, and your tasks from the module is now available and is listed in the tasks table.</p><p><note type="important">Your module canâ€™t exceed 1Mb in size.</note></p></info></step></steps></taskbody></task>